In this proclamation, President Barack Obama recognizes Human Rights Day, Bill of Rights Day, and Human Rights Week. He emphasizes the importance of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, which declares the inherent dignity and equal rights of all human beings. He states that protecting these rights leads to stability, security, and success for countries. In the United States, these rights are enshrined in the Declaration of Independence, Constitution, and Bill of Rights. Obama calls on Americans to strive to live up to these ideals and to stand in solidarity with those who seek these rights around the world. He proclaims December 10th as Human Rights Day, December 15th as Bill of Rights Day, and the week beginning December 10th as Human Rights Week. He encourages people to commemorate these observances with appropriate ceremonies and activities.